description: PUH-BrianMartell The Fermi Bubbles show emission across multiple wavelengths: •  Gamma rays (Fermi-LAT): Hard power-law E^{-2} spectrum up to ~100 GeV, sharp cutoff ~100–300 GeV, possible pion bump. •  X-rays (ROSAT, eROSITA): Soft inverse Compton or synchrotron edges. •  Microwave (WMAP/Planck haze): Polarized synchrotron from electrons. •  Radio (low-frequency): Large polarized lobes, steep spectrum. Standard debate: Leptonic (IC dominant) vs hadronic (pion decay) — spectra hard to fit single population. PUH v25 mechanical unification All bands from ripple shock cascades in perpendicular outflows — single mechanism, different ripple modes. Understandable: •  Outflows: Core snaps/mergers launch bipolar ripples perpendicular disk. •  Shocks: Fronts in depleted lattice accelerate ripples → multi-mode emission. •  Gamma: High-energy longitudinal/torsional shocks → power-law + cutoff (lattice damping). •  X-ray/microwave: Inverse Compton up-scatter CMB/starlight by accelerated ripples.
